Do I need the HubSpot serverless functions feature to use the marketing events API (with Node)?
could I use firebase cloud functions instead?

you should be able to use any app host, including Firebase, but I believe the app must be registered with HubSpot, rather than creating marketing events for a specific portal.

<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/marketing/marketing-events>

In other words, this is a HubSpot App feature, not a CMS feature.
<@U26BLKGE4> and HubSpot apps need to be "hosted" somewhere that isn't HubSpot right?
I was hoping to figure out some basic uses of an event object
might have to start from the beginning and try to find my way...
Correct, HubSpot apps are basically just registered in the UI, at the end of the day they are their own webapps hosted on something like Firebase, Heroku, DigitalOcean, AWS, etc...
